JOHANNESBURG - The passing of Nelson Mandela brought the country to a standstill. He died on this day three years ago. READ: Remembering Madiba Despite being out of the public eye for many years, he remained the people's president and a unifying figure. The Nelson Mandela Foundation will mark the anniversary of the former statesman's passing with an event taking place in Houghton, Johannesburg. Speakers include Deputy President Cyril Ramaphosa, Deputy Minister of Public Service and Administration Ayanda Dlodlo and Dr Leon Wessels.  eNCA